<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Warning, this may only work when the moon orbiting Norrath turns an odd shade of blue:<P>How to defeat yellow Deepwater Crocs at level 17. <P>The process is a obvious one. I'm just posting this to encourage dissoulusioned wizards who feel they are too delicate to solo.<P>Firstly position yourself upon the crest of a sand dune, casting Shadow Step from the bottom  will only produce a dazzling array of lights. Target a yellow Deepwater Croc and root it. Then cast Firestorm, a level 12 AE spell, which deals out 28 damage over three rounds, enabling you to nuke it with the most powerful DD in your arsenal while fire still rains down from heaven and while your ever tenuous root still holds. It's a faster way to kill the villain. In my lucky case, the Croc died where I rooted it - yes even with one full resist - and I left the scene unscathed without having to Shadow Step. The total drain of mana was well worth the experience gained.<P>I hope this strategy might continue through advanced levels.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
