<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'd say you got very lucky with that croc. I went from 16-20 in Oasis and with any croc even con or higher root would rarely take and if it did it would not hold long.  And when root did hold it was very common to go oom with the croc at a sliver of health, with root wearing as I tried to med for another blast (they have lot's of hp). Melee to finish it off is not really an option because they hit so hard and they don't have a run stage.<P>I'm not saying you can't do it as I have occasionally as well, but you're better off finding a partner since in most cases you'll be running for zone or yelling for help.  Even if you're lucky enough to get the kill it's not fun medding 7 minutes to full and you could have killed 2 crocs by then with a partner and gotten more xp.<P>My int was around 150 at the time and had some +mana gear as well and still ran out of mana trying this more often than not.<P>All said and done it's still fun to do while waiting for group but not efficient for leveling IMHO.  Make sure to shieldskin and fireshield before fight.  Seriously, that fire shield might actually provide the few extra damage you needed to take it down, and you WILL get hit because root will not hold most cases.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
