<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Now i read post after post talking about using shadowsteps and yonders in everyday battles.  In my experience (btw i keep all casting skills maxed)  i only go farther than i could have run in the same time about once ever two or three casts.  maybe you guys get lucky with it or something, but ive found it completly useless for this kind of situation.  you have to fight lots and lots of mobs to get your level up, and if your plan of battle only succeeds thirty percent of the time, your going to be leveling fast allright; in the opposite direction!  i ask of you, what do you do when the shadowstep fails?  you probably go for another root.  so why not just stay as far from the croc as you can, running in between spells, and then you can get off a root as he runs towards you (which your gonna have to do everytime you fail to step as far as you need to)
</FONT>
