<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Gonna get nailed for this I'm sure...<P>Do any wizards specialize in Alteration?  I ask because Enchanters almost always do (play a 35 chanter too) and even though EVERY chanter will say Flux (stun) and Root, I just Root them.  It casts in 2 seconds, and if you specialize Alteration you almost NEVER get interrupted.<P>BTW... how fast does the wizzy stun cast?  If it's decent, I'll stun/root to relock the mob when I'm of level.  Color Flux is only 4 seconds, and account 1 second to spells ungreying... leaving 3 seconds to cast.  (When I DO stun/root, I stun... step back a second, then Root... buys another .5 seconds for Root to hit.)<P>Is specializing Alteration a crazy notion?  Getting Root off on the first try every time seems just as important as nuking one last time...<P>Quintius the Wizard<BR>9th trial, Tholuxe Paells<P>and<P>Xornn Mier'noen<BR>35th trial, The Nameless<BR>
