Actually, I would have to say that specializing in Alteration DOES have its advantages.<P>Your gates, portals, and evacuations would be your primary spells, as well as your snares and roots. Of course, if you were looking for a group, you'd have to explain to groups that you're not what's considered a common Wizard.<P>You'd be somewhat valuable to a "tank-only" group, being able to keep the mobs back, and taking everyone away when need be, without fail/fizzle.... not sure how good you'd be protecting yourself though, other than being able to run from trouble for sure..<P>in fact,.. if i had time to build up a second wizard, i'd try it myself, just to see how easily i could get away from pk'rs on RZ. (i never fight them... if i know i can't get away, i start bagging)<P>
