all specialization does is:<BR>1. less fizzling<BR>2. less mana<BR>every time you cast a spell the game rolls on your specialization level to see if you get one of the 2.   therefore, the less mana doesnt' mean jack when you have 1000+ mana and the less fizzling wont mean jack if you aren't fizzling in the first place.<P>also, someone said you would use gates,ports, and evacs for primary spells; that is such a crock.  some people still think that if you specialize in alt then your evac wont take as long to case, this is crap.  as for less mana, if you dont have enough mana to get the spell off when you dont get specialization then you cant attempt to start casting it.  if you do have enough to cast an evac, then who cares if your sitting in NK with half a bubble or oom
