Well, I've been specialized in Evocation for my entire career.  Since about level 30, I've been able to get gate or root off in the most hellish of circumstances.  Occasionally, I might have some bad luck.  But the vast majority of the time, I can channel through hits to get a root or gate off.<P>So... specialize in evocation.  You can really see the effects in the upper levels.  I've partnered with mages specialized in conjuration (but casting evocation dd) and they were amazed by the amount of mana I SEEMED to have.  Of course, I told him that specialization was just kicking in alot AND my dds are a bit more efficient than his.<P>Finally, I'm not against experimenting in any way.  If you'd like to specialize in something else then, by all means, feel free.  And let us other, more traditional Wizards, know how it all works out!  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>Sabbok<BR>52 Wizard<BR>Bristlebane
