<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A work around for those 'unspecialized' line of spells (Specialization = Evoc for wizards) you can get the same basic effect of not being interrupted by maxxing out your dexterity.<P>Get the gear!<P>Why do you think enchanters can recover and still cast with mobs beating on them - check out chanter based gear .. charisma for landing spells and dexterity for casting thru getting hit.<P>That said - also max your casting skills every level (5 points a level) by casting baby stuff on yourself. It takes about an hour (or less) to max these skills (all 5 - specialization and channeling are maxxing at the same time for net effect of raising 7 skill levels). This reduces your fizzle rate significantly. With the new skill numbers listed on your skill chart (recent patch - above 100 a numeric value is placed in the list) you can tell what you need to work on.<P>Now, question - and I am sure it is too much to dream for - but VI recently added a memblur/hate list whipe type effect to interzone port spells. I assume this applies only to the post 50 interzone evac spells. Has anyone tested this on the shadowstep line? Would be way cool if aggro was reduced with these spells.<P>Graffenlaff Delaffensa<BR>53 Wandering Wizard - Luclin
