</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Yes, when you cast, it checks for interrupt twice, once based on damage you took during casting, and once based on how far you have moved (all hits push you a little bit).<BR>If you root yourself, you avoid the second check.<P>This is why even rooted, you still get interrupted at times, and even with a skin spell you still get interrupted at times.  I haven't tested it, but I theorize that you could be uninterruptable if you had both a skin and root up, assuming the skin holds up (someone check this?).
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
